      textEn: [
        "Educators do not create gods, nor stone statues, nor lovers. What they must create are living people of truth, goodness, and beauty.",
        "Some say: the environment is too ordinary for creation. Yet nothing is more ordinary than a blank sheet of paper, and when Bada Shanren paints a few strokes, it becomes a priceless masterpiece.",
        "Some say: life is too monotonous for creation. Yet nothing is more monotonous than prison, and yet in prison the hexagram texts of the Book of Changes were produced, and the Song of Righteousness was born.",
        "Clearly, ordinariness and monotony are merely the excuses of the lazy. We must create the extraordinary out of the ordinary, the varied out of the monotonous.",
        "Therefore, every place is a place for creation, every day is a time for creation, every person is a creator. Let us take at least two steps forward and one step back, marching along the path of creation.",
        "Rodin said: \u2018Evil is aridity.\u2019 When the sweat has dried, the blood has dried, the passion has dried, one is rigid, dead \u2014 only the dead have no desire to create. As long as there is one drop of sweat, one drop of blood, one drop of passion, it is a palace where the spirit of creation loves to dwell, and can bloom creative flowers, bear creative fruit, and propagate a forest of creation."
      ],
